content.Text:
[Wed 2026-04-22 22:52 PDT] Add a "Smart Seasonal Recommender" feature to this ASP.NET MVC Vidly app. This feature analyzes rental patterns by season/month and recommends movies that are most popular during the current time of year.

## Architecture Pattern
Follow the existing pattern exactly:
1. **Service**: `Vidly/Services/SeasonalRecommenderService.cs`
2. **Controller**: `Vidly/Controllers/SeasonalRecommenderController.cs`
3. **View**: `Vidly/Views/SeasonalRecommender/Index.cshtml`

## Existing Code Context

**Models**: `Movie` (Id, Name, ReleaseDate, Genre, Rating, DailyRate), `Rental` (Id, CustomerId, MovieId, RentalDate, DueDate, ReturnDate, DailyRate, Status), `Genre` enum, `Customer` (Id, Name)
**Repositories**: `IMovieRepository` extends `IRepository<Movie>` with GetAll(), Get(id), Search(), etc. `IRentalRepository` extends `IRepository<Rental>` with GetAll(), GetByMovie(), GetByCustomer(), etc. `ICustomerRepository` extends `IRepository<Customer>`.
**Implementations**: `InMemoryMovieRepository`, `InMemoryRentalRepository`, `InMemoryCustomerRepository`

## Service: SeasonalRecommenderService.cs

Create in `Vidly/Services/`. Constructor takes `IMovieRepository`, `IRentalRepository`. Methods:

```csharp
// Core data structure
public class SeasonalProfile {
    public string CurrentSeason { get; set; } // "Spring", "Summer", "Fall", "Winter"
    public int CurrentMonth { get; set; }
    public List<GenreSeasonality> GenreTrends { get; set; } // genre popularity by season
    public List<MovieRecommendation> Recommendations { get; set; } // top picks for current season
    public List<SeasonalInsight> Insights { get; set; } // proactive findings
    public Dictionary<string, double> SeasonalActivity { get; set; } // rentals per season
}

public class GenreSeasonality {
    public string Genre { get; set; }
    public Dictionary<string, double> SeasonScores { get; set; } // season -> normalized score
    public string PeakSeason { get; set; }
    public double Seasonality { get; set; } // coefficient of variation - how seasonal is this genre
}

public class MovieRecommendation {
    public int MovieId { get; set; }
    public string MovieName { get; set; }
    public string Genre { get; set; }
    public int? Rating { get; set; }
    public double SeasonalScore { get; set; } // how well this movie fits current season
    public string Reason { get; set; } // why recommended
}

public class SeasonalInsight {
    public string Icon { get; set; } // emoji
    public string Title { get; set; }
    public string Description { get; set; }
    public string Severity { get; set; } // "info", "success", "warning"
}
```

Logic:
- Analyze all rentals, bucket by season (Spring=Mar-May, Summer=Jun-Aug, Fall=Sep-Nov, Winter=Dec-Feb)
- For each genre, compute rental count per season and normalize
- Calculate seasonality coefficient (std dev / mean) for each genre
- Generate recommendations: movies whose genre peaks in current season, sorted by rating then rental frequency
- Generate 3-5 proactive insights like "Horror peaks in Fall", "Romance surges in Winter", "Activity drops in Summer" etc.

## Controller: SeasonalRecommenderController.cs

```csharp
public class SeasonalRecommenderController : Controller {
    // Constructor with repos -> service
    // GET: SeasonalRecommender -> Index view with SeasonalProfile
    // GET: SeasonalRecommender/Json -> JSON endpoint
    // GET: SeasonalRecommender/Season/{name} -> filtered view for specific season
}
```

## View: Index.cshtml

Create a rich interactive dashboard. Use inline CSS/JS (the app doesn't use bundling for feature views). Include:

1. **Season Banner** - large current season display with icon (🌸🌞🍂❄️) and date
2. **Activity Chart** - Canvas bar chart showing rentals per season, current season highlighted
3. **Genre Heatmap** - HTML table showing genre × season with color intensity based on popularity
4. **Recommendations Grid** - cards for top 10 movie picks with score, genre badge, rating stars, reason
5. **Insights Panel** - proactive findings with icons and severity colors
6. **Season Selector** - buttons to preview recommendations for other seasons
7. **Export** - JSON download button

Style: modern dark theme with seasonal accent colors (spring=green, summer=gold, fall=orange, winter=blue). Responsive layout.

The view model is `@model Vidly.Services.SeasonalRecommenderService+SeasonalProfile` (or define the classes at namespace level in the service file).

## Important
- Put all model classes at namespace level in the service file (not nested) so the view can reference them
- Use `namespace Vidly.Services` for the service
- Use `namespace Vidly.Controllers` for the controller  
- The controller constructor should use `new InMemoryMovieRepository()` and `new InMemoryRentalRepository()` as defaults (same pattern as other controllers)
- Add `using Vidly.Repositories;` and `using Vidly.Services;` in the controller
- Do NOT modify any existing files
- Create only the 3 new files listed above
